{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "pulsify-profile-001",
    "name": "Pulsify - User Profiles Module",
    "description": "Complete test collection for User Profile endpoints (Module 2)\n\n**Architecture:** Routes → Auth Middleware → Joi Validation → Controller → Service → Repository → Model\n\n**Base URL:** http://localhost:3000/api/v1\n\n**Setup:**\n1. Select 'Local Development' environment\n2. Run 'Login' request first to get JWT token (auto-saved)\n3. All protected routes will use the saved token automatically",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{ACCESS_TOKEN}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "00 - Auth (Setup)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register New User",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const response = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Status is 201 Created\", () => {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (response.user) {",
                  "    pm.test(\"Response contains user object\", () => {",
                  "        pm.expect(response.user).to.have.property('user_id');",
                  "        pm.expect(response.user).to.have.property('email');",
                  "        pm.expect(response.user).to.have.property('username');",
                  "    });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{TEST_USER_EMAIL}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{TEST_USER_PASSWORD}}\",\n  \"username\": \"testuser\",\n  \"display_name\": \"Test User\",\n  \"date_of_birth\": \"1995-01-15\",\n  \"gender\": \"prefer-not-to-say\",\n  \"country\": \"US\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{BASE_URL}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "register"]
            },
            "description": "Register a new test user. Run this first if you don't have a user yet."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Login (Auto-saves Token)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const response = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "// Auto-save token for all subsequent requests",
                  "if (response.access_token) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set(\"ACCESS_TOKEN\", response.access_token);",
                  "    console.log(\"✅ Token saved:\", response.access_token);",
                  "}",
                  "",
                  "if (response.user && response.user.user_id) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set(\"CURRENT_USER_ID\", response.user.user_id);",
                  "    console.log(\"✅ User ID saved:\", response.user.user_id);",
                  "}",
                  "",
                  "// Assertions",
                  "pm.test(\"Status is 200 OK\", () => {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has access_token\", () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(response).to.have.property(\"access_token\");",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has user object\", () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(response).to.have.property(\"user\");",
                  "    pm.expect(response.user).to.have.property(\"user_id\");",
                  "    pm.expect(response.user).to.have.property(\"email\");",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{TEST_USER_EMAIL}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{TEST_USER_PASSWORD}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{BASE_URL}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "**RUN THIS FIRST!**\n\nLogs in and automatically saves the JWT token to `{{ACCESS_TOKEN}}`.\n\nAll subsequent requests will use this token for authentication."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "Authentication endpoints to get your JWT token. Run Login first!"
    },
    {
      "name": "01 - Profile (Protected)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get My Profile",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const response = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Status is 200 OK\", () => {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response contains private fields\", () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(response).to.have.property('email');",
                  "    pm.expect(response).to.have.property('is_private');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response contains public fields\", () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(response).to.have.property('username');",
                  "    pm.expect(response).to.have.property('display_name');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}/users/me",
              "host": ["{{BASE_URL}}"],
              "path": ["users", "me"]
            },
            "description": "**Layer Flow:**\n1. ✅ Auth Middleware validates JWT\n2. ✅ Service retrieves user from database\n3. ✅ Returns PRIVATE profile (includes email)\n\n**Expected:** 200 OK with private profile data"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Update My Profile",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const response = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Status is 200 OK\", () => {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Profile was updated\", () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(response).to.have.property('display_name');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"display_name\": \"John Doe Updated\",\n  \"bio\": \"Music producer and DJ from NYC\",\n  \"location\": \"New York, USA\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}/users/me",
              "host": ["{{BASE_URL}}"],
              "path": ["users", "me"]
            },
            "description": "**Layer Flow:**\n1. ✅ Auth Middleware\n2. ✅ Joi validates display_name (max 50), bio (max 500)\n3. ✅ Service updates only allowed fields\n4. ✅ Repository saves to DB\n\n**Expected:** 200 OK with updated profile"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Public Profile",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const response = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Status is 200 OK\", () => {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response does NOT contain private fields\", () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(response).to.not.have.property('email');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response contains public fields\", () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(response).to.have.property('username');",
                  "    pm.expect(response).to.have.property('display_name');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}/users/{{CURRENT_USER_ID}}",
              "host": ["{{BASE_URL}}"],
              "path": ["users", "{{CURRENT_USER_ID}}"]
            },
            "description": "**Layer Flow:**\n1. ✅ NO auth required (public route)\n2. ✅ Service checks user exists\n3. ✅ Returns PUBLIC profile (NO email)\n\n**Expected:** 200 OK with public profile only"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Search Users",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const response = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Status is 200 OK\", () => {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has data array\", () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(response).to.have.property('data');",
                  "    pm.expect(response.data).to.be.an('array');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has pagination\", () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(response).to.have.property('pagination');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}/users?q=test&page=1&limit=20",
              "host": ["{{BASE_URL}}"],
              "path": ["users"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "q",
                  "value": "test"
                },
                {
                  "key": "page",
                  "value": "1"
                },
                {
                  "key": "limit",
                  "value": "20"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Search users with pagination"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "02 - Error Testing (Auth)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "401 - Missing Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status is 401 Unauthorized\", () => {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(401);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}/users/me",
              "host": ["{{BASE_URL}}"],
              "path": ["users", "me"]
            },
            "description": "Test: Auth middleware rejects missing token\nExpected: 401 Unauthorized"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "401 - Invalid Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status is 401 Unauthorized\", () => {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(401);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "INVALID_TOKEN_123",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}/users/me",
              "host": ["{{BASE_URL}}"],
              "path": ["users", "me"]
            },
            "description": "Test: Auth middleware rejects invalid JWT\nExpected: 401 Unauthorized"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "03 - Error Testing (Validation)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "400 - Bio Too Long",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status is 400 Bad Request\", () => {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(400);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"bio\": \"Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris.\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}/users/me",
              "host": ["{{BASE_URL}}"],
              "path": ["users", "me"]
            },
            "description": "Test: Joi catches bio > 500 characters\nExpected: 400 Bad Request"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "400 - Display Name Too Long",
          "event": [
            {
